      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PHAROAH'S GLORY (3) switches to synthetic for the first time. She was in the market but failed to fire at Swan Hill last time out, now coming back a notch or two in grade. The win prior, albeit on heavy ground, was dominant and she's certainly up to this on class if she handles the surface. GOOD HARMONY (5) had her first run on a synthetic track last time at Pakenham and ran well for third having contested a much tougher race at Flemington prior. She'll be hard to hold out. JAZ TYCOON (1) is racing well with two wins from his past three. He won well here last time out in a similar race and is now 2/2 here which is key on a tricky track to get a read on. TRADEWORX (8) likes it here having missed the placings for the first time on this track last start and he finished fourth. Drops 3kg for this and has claims. ZEACTION (4) can run well first go on synthetic.",
